WEBVTT

NOTE
Q2 Planning Sync - March 26, 2026
Participants: Ankit (Engineering Lead), Priya (HR Manager), Mrinal (Product Manager)

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
<v Ankit>Morning, everyone. Let's get started with the Q2 planning review.

00:00:05.500 --> 00:00:12.000
<v Ankit>First, we need to update the PROJ-1 ticket because the API migration schedule has shifted.

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:18.500
<v Ankit>I'll own that change. Move the deadline out to April 10th so the team has proper buffer.

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:24.000
<v Priya>That works. On hiring, we still need to open the backend role as soon as possible.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:32.000
<v Priya>I'll act as the hiring manager, and I want the new hire to start by March 28th if we can make that happen.

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:39.000
<v Priya>This is for a Senior Backend Engineer on the Platform Engineering team.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:46.000
<v Mrinal>Next, we need to handle the cloud budget issue before it becomes a blocker.

00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:54.000
<v Mrinal>Let's raise the AWS spend limit by 40k for the quarter. I'll submit and own that procurement request.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:01:01.000
<v Mrinal>We need approval by end of day today, March 26th, or we risk running into service issues.

00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:08.000
<v Mrinal>Also, I want a new Jira ticket created for the mobile app performance optimization workstream.

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:16.000
<v Mrinal>Put it in the PROJ project, mark it high priority, assign it to me, and target completion by April 1st.

00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:23.000
<v Ankit>One more thing: we should revisit the pricing model soon.

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
<v Ankit>I don't want to turn that into an action item yet, but keep it on the radar.

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:33.000
<v Priya>Agreed. We can pick that up in a later meeting once the hiring and infrastructure work is moving.

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:38.000
<v Mrinal>That covers my side. Thanks, everyone.

00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:42.000
<v Ankit>Thanks all. Let's close it out there.
